President Biden delivered remarks in the East Room of the White House, thanking Secretary of Veterans Affairs Denis McDonough, veteran service organizations, and Democratic and Republican sponsors of the bill. He emphasized the importance of caring for military veterans and their families, stating that veterans are the backbone of the country. He discussed the PACT Act, which extends benefits and services to veterans exposed to burn pits and toxic substances during their service. President Biden signed nine bills with bipartisan support that improve care for veterans and honor their service. These bills include providing preventative care for veterans exposed to burn pits, improving breast imaging services, compensating Americans who developed cancer from World War Two-era nuclear programs, and honoring veterans through various means. President Biden pledged his administration's commitment to supporting veterans and their families, stating that his administration will always have their back.